/ --- width bump tests ---
bz zb 600#"A"    / 600 A's → 9→10 bit bump
bz zb 1200#"B"   / 1200 B's → 10→11 bit bump
bz zb 2500#"C"   / 2500 C's → 11→12 bit bump

/ --- reset/clear code test ---
bz zb ,/600#,"AB"  / alternating AB, triggers reset

/ --- truncation / corruption test ---
e:zb "hello world"
bz e                / should decode fine
\e 0
bz e[0 1 2 3 4]     / truncated, length error

\\
